<stack-static>
    <statement><p><p>
Expand and simplify:
<m> {\left(1-2 x\right) \left(5 x+4\right)} </m>
</p>
<p>
Enter your answer in fully expanded form.
<br/><br/>
<fillin characters="8" name="ans1"/>


</p></p></statement>
    <solution><p><h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>To expand the expression</p>

<p>
<m>
{\left(1-2 x\right) \left(5 x+4\right)}
</m>
</p>

<p>we use the distributive property, multiplying each term in the first bracket by each term in the second bracket.</p>

<p><alert>Step 1: Multiply the first terms</alert></p>

<p>
<m>
({5}x)({-2}x) = {-10}x^2
</m>
</p>

<p><alert>Step 2: Multiply the outer terms</alert></p>

<p>
<m>
({5}x)({1}) = {5}x
</m>
</p>

<p><alert>Step 3: Multiply the inner terms</alert></p>

<p>
<m>
({4})({-2}x) = {-8}x
</m>
</p>

<p><alert>Step 4: Multiply the last terms</alert></p>

<p>
<m>
({4})({1}) = {4}
</m>
</p>

<p><alert>Step 5: Combine like terms</alert></p>

<p>The linear terms must be added together:</p>

<p>
<m>
{5}x + {-8}x = {-3}x
</m>
</p>

<p><alert>Final Answer:</alert></p>

<p>
<m>
{-10 x^2-3 x+4}
</m>
</p>

<p>Remember: when multiplying two binomials, every term in the first bracket must multiply every term in the second bracket, and like terms must be collected at the end.</p></p></solution>
    <answer><p><m>-10 x^2-3 x+4</m></p></answer>
</stack-static>